      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HOT SAKI (1) was quickly into stride and burnt early from out wide where he gave a sight, finishing second (21.93) and beaten one length over 390m at Ballarat. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card last start despite being beaten. Racing well and deserves a win. PAW CLARISSA (3) has a strong record this track and trip with five wins and two placings from eight starts. In the money last time at Shepparton (22.16) in a Grade 4/5, finishing a 1.5 lengths second. Can feature with the right run. PAW JELANI (2) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fifth (22.43) last time in a Grade 5 H at Ballarat. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. One of the main contenders. PAW KRAMER (7) has top-three aspirations after placing last time.",
